com.amazon.insights
Interface Event

public interface Event

Represents the visit or conversion event of an A/B test, or may also be used to collect useful information in your application.

The example below demonstrates how to record view and conversion events. The "level1Complete" event represents the view event, and if the user makes a purchase, the code below records a "level1UserBoughtUpgrade" event as the conversion event. 

    // get the event client from your insights instance
    EventClient eventClient = insightsInstance.getEventClient();

    // create and record the view event
    Event level1CompleteEvent = eventClient.createEvent("level1Complete");
    eventClient.recordEvent(level1CompleteEvent);
 
    // record if the user bought an upgrade (conversion)
    if (userBoughtUpgrade) {
        Event level1UserBoughtUpgradeEvent = eventClient.createEvent("level1UserBoughtUpgrade");
        eventClient.recordEvent(level1UserBoughtUpgradeEvent);
    }
